1
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:17,166
♪ ♪

2
00:00:17,250 --> 00:00:21,041
Oh, wow. This is the coolest
thing I've ever seen.

3
00:00:21,125 --> 00:00:23,291
My glasses!

4
00:00:25,625 --> 00:00:28,041
It's so steamy.
I can barely see!

5
00:00:28,125 --> 00:00:30,416
Don't they seem a little
amateurish to you?

6
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:34,333
If by amateurish you mean
totally bad ass, then oh yeah.

7
00:00:35,958 --> 00:00:38,916
Kazu? Is that who I think it is?

8
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:39,916
Sure is.

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,958
[CHEERLEADERS]
Let's go, Peaches!

10
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:44,916
[CROWD cheers]

11
00:00:52,625 --> 00:00:55,000
I wanna do that routine
at the school festival.

12
00:00:55,083 --> 00:00:57,791
Just like my parents
did back in college.

13
00:00:59,791 --> 00:01:01,625
[KAZUMA] It was their first
performance as a group,

14
00:01:01,708 --> 00:01:03,416
so I think it should
be ours, too.

15
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:04,791
I still can't believe
your old man

16
00:01:04,875 --> 00:01:06,791
was your mom's
Cheerleading Coach.

17
00:01:06,875 --> 00:01:08,958
It's great that you have
this video as a momento

18
00:01:09,041 --> 00:01:10,250
of their time together.

19
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:11,833
If your folks made it
all the way to the

20
00:01:11,916 --> 00:01:14,333
World Championships, they
must have been quite a pair.

21
00:01:14,416 --> 00:01:17,625
I used to hear stories
about it all the time.

22
00:01:17,708 --> 00:01:19,250
They remind me of our team.

23
00:01:19,333 --> 00:01:21,125
They started with seven members.

24
00:01:21,208 --> 00:01:23,416
But they worked hard to made
the most of what they had.

25
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:24,916
Makes sense.

26
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,250
So, that's why you were so
obsessed with the number seven.

27
00:01:27,333 --> 00:01:28,500
Brilliant!

28
00:01:28,583 --> 00:01:30,208
This plan saves us from
having to choreograph

29
00:01:30,291 --> 00:01:31,125
a routine ourselves!

30
00:01:31,208 --> 00:01:32,500
Wataru. Not the point.

31
00:01:32,583 --> 00:01:35,125
[stomach growling]

32
00:01:35,208 --> 00:01:36,500
[KAZUMA laughs]

33
00:01:36,583 --> 00:01:38,666
Listen. It won't
be easy to learn,

34
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:41,958
but if my parents could
do it, then so can we!

35
00:01:42,041 --> 00:01:45,583
I'm in. Let's do
it together, guys!

36
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:48,875
Yeah!

37
00:01:48,958 --> 00:01:50,041
We're agreed.

38
00:01:50,125 --> 00:01:51,916
[TON] It is gonna be
a challenge though.

39
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,166
The festival's still
two months away.

40
00:01:54,250 --> 00:01:55,875
If we practice as
hard as we can,

41
00:01:55,958 --> 00:01:57,541
I know we'll be ready to go.

42
00:01:57,625 --> 00:01:58,791
Plus, it doesn't hurt

43
00:01:58,875 --> 00:02:00,666
to have the Master of
Tumbling on our team.

44
00:02:00,750 --> 00:02:03,041
The toughest part of this
routine is the first stunt.

45
00:02:03,125 --> 00:02:05,000
It's gonna take some doing.

46
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:06,875
It requires a mid-air back flip.

47
00:02:06,958 --> 00:02:09,041
That's no small feat
for any flyer.

48
00:02:09,125 --> 00:02:11,583
We only need one stunt
group to attempt the move.

49
00:02:11,666 --> 00:02:14,666
But if we don't get it exactly
right, we're dead in the water.

50
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:16,541
Kazu. Can you do it?

51
00:02:16,625 --> 00:02:20,250
'Course I can, but I'm not the
only candidate for this stunt.

52
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:21,416
Isn't that right, buddy?

53
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:23,833
[gasps] I can't.

54
00:02:23,916 --> 00:02:26,000
Don't forget, we're
the Breakers, dude.

55
00:02:26,083 --> 00:02:27,708
Let's break through
this together!

56
00:02:27,791 --> 00:02:29,541
[HARUKI]
Huh...

57
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:34,000
All right then.

58
00:02:34,083 --> 00:02:36,666
Well, we have time, so let's
get closer to the event

59
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:39,500
and see how you progress
before we make our choice.

60
00:02:39,583 --> 00:02:40,250
[knocking]

61
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:41,416
[WATARU]
Hm?

62
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:43,208
[WATARU'S MOTHER]
I'm coming in, Wataru.

63
00:02:43,291 --> 00:02:44,750
[WATARU]
Uh!

64
00:02:44,833 --> 00:02:47,416
I am so sorry for disturbing you
during your video research.

65
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:50,333
But I wish to say thank you for
all you've done for Wataru.

66
00:02:50,416 --> 00:02:51,583
Dinner is ready.

67
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:54,583
Would you boys care to
join us for a nice meal?

68
00:02:59,416 --> 00:03:01,583
[ICHIRO] Dude. Your mom's
all right for an old girl.

69
00:03:01,666 --> 00:03:03,625
[GEN]
No. She looks just like Wataru.

70
00:03:03,708 --> 00:03:04,750
[ICHIRO]
Uh.

71
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:06,583
[stomach growls]

72
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:09,500
[HARUKI]
Can we shut up and go eat?

73
00:04:41,583 --> 00:04:43,916
[WATARU]
Special delivery!

74
00:04:45,291 --> 00:04:46,208
Hey guys.

75
00:04:46,291 --> 00:04:48,125
[ALL chuckle]

76
00:04:48,208 --> 00:04:49,333
[GEN]
Ichiro, hold it up!

77
00:04:49,416 --> 00:04:50,875
[ICHIRO]
What do you think I'm doing?

78
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:52,291
[KAZUMA] You're the one
who needs to rotate...

79
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:53,958
[HARUKI]
Come in.

80
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:58,375
[WATARU sighs]
That was great!

81
00:04:58,458 --> 00:04:59,708
Glad you had fun.

82
00:04:59,791 --> 00:05:01,916
How boutcha give me a little
heads up next time?

83
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,750
[WATARU] This is exactly what
Dreams practices with.

84
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:06,375
We can't have second-rate
equipment.

85
00:05:06,458 --> 00:05:09,833
[ICHIRO] Hey, Wataru, how much
did this stuff set you back?

86
00:05:09,916 --> 00:05:12,958
Unclear. I choose not to look
at price tags while shopping.

87
00:05:13,041 --> 00:05:14,416
How loaded are you?

88
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:15,708
It's a good step.

89
00:05:15,791 --> 00:05:17,583
Having the right equipment
makes a difference.

90
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:20,208
Guys! Let's practice
our butts off.

91
00:05:20,291 --> 00:05:23,541
Maybe we'll get lucky and
score ourselves some dates.

92
00:05:23,625 --> 00:05:25,208
[HARUKI gasping]

93
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:28,250
One, two and down and up!

94
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:29,708
[HARUKI yelps]

95
00:05:29,791 --> 00:05:30,833
--[GEN] We gotcha!
--[WATARU] Nice try!

96
00:05:30,916 --> 00:05:34,541
[gasps] Guys. I'm so sorry.

97
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:36,958
It's not that I don't trust
the bases. I swear.

98
00:05:37,041 --> 00:05:39,375
My mind knows I'm safe,
but my body--

99
00:05:39,458 --> 00:05:40,958
Look. It's fine.

100
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:43,833
You've got the basic idea
of the Elevator down.

101
00:05:43,916 --> 00:05:45,500
I think you and Kazu
should start working

102
00:05:45,583 --> 00:05:47,125
on your jumps and flips next.

103
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:48,916
[KAZUMA]
Cool!

104
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,166
[HARUKI]
Uh...

105
00:05:53,125 --> 00:05:54,458
[SHO]
All right.

106
00:05:54,541 --> 00:05:55,750
Listen to me carefully:

107
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,958
push down without bending
your knees too much,

108
00:05:58,041 --> 00:05:59,750
then jump while fully
extending your legs

109
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:01,458
and raising your hands
above your head.

110
00:06:01,541 --> 00:06:03,583
Once you feel steady,
hug your knees to your chest

111
00:06:03,666 --> 00:06:06,375
as tight as you can
and then flip backwards.

112
00:06:10,916 --> 00:06:14,000
[SHO] Kazu looks like he's got
it down. You're next Haru.

113
00:06:14,083 --> 00:06:15,583
You ready?

114
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:26,083
[SHO]
Haru!

115
00:06:26,166 --> 00:06:27,958
[crash]

116
00:06:29,583 --> 00:06:32,208
It's all right if you wanna
stick to small jumps for now.

117
00:06:32,291 --> 00:06:33,208
No need to rush.

118
00:06:33,291 --> 00:06:34,583
I'm fine.

119
00:06:34,666 --> 00:06:35,208
[KAZUMA]
Haru.

120
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:36,625
[HARUKI gasps]

121
00:06:36,708 --> 00:06:39,416
Just give it time, man.

122
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,916
[HARUKI exhales]

123
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:48,958
Now say it with me, everyone!
Let's go Meishiin!

124
00:06:49,041 --> 00:06:52,791
[STUDENTS muttering]

125
00:06:52,875 --> 00:06:53,958
Thank you, Haru.

126
00:06:54,041 --> 00:06:56,250
It's really nice to
see such enthusiasm.

127
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:59,041
But I'm afraid your presentation
got a little bit off topic.

128
00:06:59,125 --> 00:07:03,916
[ICHIRO, KAZUMA laughing]

129
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,333
By the way, gentlemen.

130
00:07:05,416 --> 00:07:07,541
Starting next semester, my son
will be studying here;

131
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:09,208
he's an extremely
sensitive young man

132
00:07:09,291 --> 00:07:12,166
so I'd appreciate it if
you'd be nice to him.

133
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:17,291
[CAFE MANAGER 1A] Shaved ice
with a sunflowery summer theme!

134
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:19,791
[ALL]
All right! Let's dig in!

135
00:07:26,791 --> 00:07:29,625
Are you kidding me man?
Do you ever lose your cool?

136
00:07:29,708 --> 00:07:32,583
[KAZUMA]
Where're Ton and Wataru?

137
00:07:32,666 --> 00:07:34,583
They have one class
left, I think.

138
00:07:34,666 --> 00:07:37,833
[GEN] Lame. Well, I finished
my last final yesterday!

139
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:39,125
[ICHIRO]
You finished it,

140
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:41,500
but do you think you
actually passed this time?

141
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:42,708
[GEN]
Dude...

142
00:07:42,791 --> 00:07:43,916
[ICHIRO] You suck at
Chinese and you know it!

143
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,333
[GEN]
Mind your own business!

144
00:07:45,416 --> 00:07:47,625
[laughs] Get ready, cause
starting tomorrow morning,

145
00:07:47,708 --> 00:07:49,416
we meet in the park every day.

146
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:52,208
Then after lunch we make a
company move to the rooftop.

147
00:07:52,291 --> 00:07:53,833
We're gonna eat,
sleep, and breathe

148
00:07:53,916 --> 00:07:55,833
cheerleading this summer.

149
00:07:57,208 --> 00:07:59,333
Hey, Ichiro. What's
with the wrist band?

150
00:07:59,416 --> 00:08:00,625
Never seen it before.

151
00:08:00,708 --> 00:08:03,625
Huh? Oh, yeah.
Ain't it awesome?

152
00:08:03,708 --> 00:08:05,875
No, it's not,
why are you wearing it?

153
00:08:05,958 --> 00:08:08,458
It was a present from
my super-hot girlfriend.

154
00:08:08,541 --> 00:08:11,708
Not! I'm still single!

155
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:13,250
Show me your wrist!

156
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:15,125
[ICHIRO grunts]

157
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:17,708
[ALL gasping]

158
00:08:17,791 --> 00:08:19,250
[gasps]

159
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:21,208
Oh, right. That.

160
00:08:21,291 --> 00:08:23,125
It's no biggie.
I sprained it at work.

161
00:08:23,208 --> 00:08:25,083
Why didn't you tell us sooner?

162
00:08:25,166 --> 00:08:27,583
[HARUKI] Any idea how
long it'll take to heal?

163
00:08:27,666 --> 00:08:30,000
The Doctor said four weeks,
but screw that!

164
00:08:30,083 --> 00:08:32,083
I can be ready to go
in half that time!

165
00:08:32,166 --> 00:08:34,750
I'm sorry, Ichiro, but if the
Doctor told you four weeks,

166
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:36,208
then that's what it's gotta be.

167
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:39,000
Relax! All I have to do
is tape it up every day

168
00:08:39,083 --> 00:08:40,250
and then it'll be good as new!

169
00:08:40,333 --> 00:08:41,750
No way.

170
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:44,208
We're about to start tossing
and catching practice soon.

171
00:08:44,291 --> 00:08:46,125
You can't risk aggravating
it or even worse,

172
00:08:46,208 --> 00:08:48,083
getting another injury.

173
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:51,708
[sighs] Whatever you say, Sho.

174
00:08:59,375 --> 00:09:02,666
[WATARU]
One, two, down, up, down, up!

175
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,458
Gen. You gotta tighten
up that grip!

176
00:09:06,541 --> 00:09:09,333
Use the force from the
load-in to propel him up!

177
00:09:09,416 --> 00:09:11,583
Ton, you're still not
using your knees properly.

178
00:09:11,666 --> 00:09:12,291
[BOTH]
Right.

179
00:09:12,375 --> 00:09:13,875
[SHO]
And Wataru,

180
00:09:13,958 --> 00:09:15,875
during the cradle you have to
watch the flyer more carefully.

181
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:18,333
Catch him with your entire
body, not just your arms.

182
00:09:18,416 --> 00:09:19,541
Understood!

183
00:09:19,625 --> 00:09:21,875
[SHO]
Kazu, your prep jump is too big.

184
00:09:21,958 --> 00:09:24,333
And you can't control
your posture mid-air.

185
00:09:24,416 --> 00:09:26,916
Pay more attention
to your body's axis.

186
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:27,625
[KAZUMA]
Right!

187
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:29,625
[SHO]
Well? Again!

188
00:09:37,541 --> 00:09:41,541
[CROWD chattering]

189
00:09:46,541 --> 00:09:47,708
Hey, man.

190
00:09:47,791 --> 00:09:50,583
I'm shocked! You managed
to get outta bed!

191
00:09:53,291 --> 00:09:54,458
[HARUKI]
By the way,

192
00:09:54,541 --> 00:09:57,208
thanks for inviting me
to practice with you.

193
00:09:57,291 --> 00:09:58,750
Back when we did Judo,

194
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:01,708
the two of us would practice in
the morning a lot, remember?

195
00:10:01,791 --> 00:10:03,416
Yeah, I guess that's true.

196
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,291
[KAZUMA] It's always way more
fun to work with a friend

197
00:10:05,375 --> 00:10:06,958
than it is to do it
all by yourself.

198
00:10:07,041 --> 00:10:09,666
Plus, we're both flyers
so it makes sense.

199
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:14,500
Kazu, listen--

200
00:10:14,583 --> 00:10:16,416
Stop worrying, man.

201
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:17,458
[gasps]

202
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:21,500
I've been around you
for a really long time.

203
00:10:21,583 --> 00:10:23,541
Whenever you struggled
with a Judo technique,

204
00:10:23,625 --> 00:10:26,125
you worked at it till it
became your specialty.

205
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:29,666
And I was right there watchin'
so don't try to argue.

206
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:33,041
[HARUKI] Hey, Kazu!
Eventually, I am gonna fly!

207
00:10:33,125 --> 00:10:34,541
[KAZUMA] Cool! But if
you wanna be the one

208
00:10:34,625 --> 00:10:37,166
to do that backflip,
you'll have to earn it!

209
00:10:42,458 --> 00:10:45,125
[SHO] It's fine if you'd rather
start with a straight up jump.

210
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:46,458
[HARUKI grunts]

211
00:10:46,541 --> 00:10:49,083
[WATARU]
One, two, down, up!

212
00:10:49,166 --> 00:10:52,541
[HARUKI whimpers]

213
00:10:52,625 --> 00:10:53,666
Careful!

214
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:54,875
[GEN]
You're okay.

215
00:10:54,958 --> 00:10:57,791
[gasps] Guys. Thanks.

216
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:00,666
Sorry.

217
00:11:00,750 --> 00:11:04,166
I guess I need to go practice it
a little more on the trampoline.

218
00:11:19,958 --> 00:11:24,583
[panting] One more time!

219
00:11:24,666 --> 00:11:27,833
♪ ♪

220
00:11:27,916 --> 00:11:31,125
[ALL]
Go! Let's go, Breakers!

221
00:11:31,208 --> 00:11:34,416
We are... B-O-Y!

222
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:37,875
Go! Let's go, Breakers!

223
00:11:37,958 --> 00:11:41,250
One... Two... Three,
are you ready?

224
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:42,625
Stop!

225
00:11:42,708 --> 00:11:45,333
[HARUKI panting]

226
00:11:45,416 --> 00:11:47,500
This sucks. We're trying,

227
00:11:47,583 --> 00:11:50,458
but no matter what we do,
we can't get in sync.

228
00:11:50,541 --> 00:11:51,833
I'm so sorry.

229
00:11:51,916 --> 00:11:54,291
I'm doing my best but
I just can't keep up.

230
00:11:54,375 --> 00:11:58,083
Until today, I had no idea my
sense of rhythm was this awful.

231
00:11:58,166 --> 00:11:59,291
It's all right!

232
00:11:59,375 --> 00:12:01,125
Just concentrate on
keeping with the count,

233
00:12:01,208 --> 00:12:02,583
pay attention to your teammates,

234
00:12:02,666 --> 00:12:04,583
and stay focused.
I know we'll get there.

235
00:12:04,666 --> 00:12:06,958
I wouldn't be so sure!

236
00:12:10,166 --> 00:12:15,000
[TON] At this rate, our debut
gonna be a total disaster.

237
00:12:15,083 --> 00:12:17,833
'Kay. Let's call it
a day, everybody.

238
00:12:17,916 --> 00:12:19,208
[ICHIRO]
No way!

239
00:12:19,291 --> 00:12:22,125
If we don't keep practicing,
we'll never be ready!

240
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:23,458
Look, man.

241
00:12:23,541 --> 00:12:25,208
I'm not saying you're wrong,
but we need a break.

242
00:12:25,291 --> 00:12:27,958
[ICHIRO] What we need is to dig
in our heels and keep working!

243
00:12:28,041 --> 00:12:29,708
You're right. And we
should start tomorrow.

244
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:31,666
[ICHIRO] Here's a quote:
"When the going gets tough,

245
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:33,791
the tough get going!"

246
00:12:33,875 --> 00:12:36,458
You can't can solve every
problem by pushing forward.

247
